      "I tested the eqJoin variant and it's only slightly faster than the getAll approach on secondary index:\r\n```\r\nr.db('example').table('posts')\r\n  .eqJoin('userKey', r.db('example').table('users'), {index: 'key'})\r\n  .map(function(joined) {\r\n    return joined('left').merge({\r\n      firstname: joined('right')('firstname'),\r\n      lastname: joined('right')('lastname')\r\n    });\r\n  })\r\n```\r\n```\r\n27 rows returned\r\n\r\n1.62s round-trip time --- 1.35s server time --- 40 shard accesses\r\n```\r\n\r\nCompared to 141ms for primary index, I'm still not impressed by the secondary indexes in RethinkDB"
